The International Monetary Fund saidit approved a 48 mln dlr loan to assist Ecuador in meeting itsforeign exchange needs following the earthquakes that struck inMarch.    The loan, which the IMF provides countries under specialcircumstances, is equal to 25 pct of Ecuador's quota, oreconomic standing, in the Fund.    The IMF said that according to recent estimates, theearthquakes will hurt the country's balance of payments thisyear because of the loss of oil revenues due to destruction ofpart of the oil pipeline. REUTER&#3;